{
  "texts": [
    "The resulting two-qubit state composition is verified from the ESR spectrum when the exchange is on.",
    "The ESR measurement after the protocol shows only two predominant transitions pertaining to |↓↓⟩, with the amplitude limited by the two-qubit exchange 38.",
    "From these spectra, we extract an initialization fidelity of 99.6%.",
    "See the Methods for the protocol details and Supplementary Information for the ESR spectra analysis.",
    "This initialization protocol is robust to low B 0, and we expect it to be limited by the fidelities of control and readout on which the protocol relies, and their time scale relative to that of spin relaxation and thermalization."
  ]
}